[2026-03-13T18:36:12Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ee3k8bxXxqeD9usER1oa4q","type":"tool_result","content":"   330→\n   331→\t// Now finalize run state\n   332→\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   333→\tif err != nil {\n   334→\t\treturn\n   335→\t}\n   336→\tif run.State == domain.RunStateRunning {\n   337→\t\tif reportedResult == \"succeeded\" {\n   338→\t\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateSucceeded)\n   339→\t\t} else if reportedResult != \"\" {\n   340→\t\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateFailed)\n   341→\t\t} else if exitCode == 0 {\n   342→\t\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateSucceeded)\n   343→\t\t} else {\n   344→\t\t\trun.Fail(fmt.Sprintf(\"container exited with code %d\", exitCode))\n   345→\t\t}\n   346→\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   347→\t}\n   348→\n   349→\t// Fire evolution trigger if configured\n   350→\tif s.evolution != nil {\n   351→\t\ts.evolution.Fire(projectDir, workflowName, runID)\n   352→\t}\n   353→\n   354→\t// Merge is handled as a workflow step in host.cloche, not here.\n   355→\n   356→\t// Container retention policy:\n   357→\t// - Failed runs: always keep the container for debugging\n   358→\t// - Successful runs + --keep-container: keep the container\n   359→\t// - Successful runs without --keep-container: remove the container\n   360→\trunFinal, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   361→\trunFailed := runFinal != nil && (runFinal.State == domain.RunStateFailed || runFinal.State == domain.RunStateCancelled)\n   362→\n   363→\tif keepContainer || runFailed {\n   364→\t\treason := \"--keep-container\"\n   365→\t\tif runFailed {\n   366→\t\t\treason = \"run failed\"\n   367→\t\t}\n   368→\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: keeping container %s (%s)\", runID, containerID, reason)\n   369→\t\tif runFinal != nil {\n   370→\t\t\trunFinal.ContainerKept = true\n   371→\t\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, runFinal)\n   372→\t\t}\n   373→\t} else {\n   374→\t\tif err := s.container.Remove(ctx, containerID); err != nil {\n   375→\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to remove container %s: %v\", runID, containerID, err)\n   376→\t\t} else {\n   377→\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: removed container %s\", runID, containerID)\n   378→\t\t}\n   379→\t}\n   380→\n   381→\t// Cleanup mapping\n   382→\ts.mu.Lock()\n   383→\tdelete(s.runIDs, runID)\n   384→\ts.mu.Unlock()\n   385→}\n   386→\n   387→func (s *ClocheServer) ListRuns(ctx context.Context, req *pb.ListRunsRequest) (*pb.ListRunsResponse, error) {\n   388→\tvar runs []*domain.Run\n   389→\tvar err error\n   390→\tif req.ProjectDir != \"\" {\n   391→\t\t// Project-scoped: no time filter (project is sufficient scoping)\n   392→\t\truns, err = s.store.ListRunsByProject(ctx, req.ProjectDir, time.Time{})\n   393→\t} else if req.All {\n   394→\t\truns, err = s.store.ListRuns(ctx, time.Time{})\n   395→\t} else {\n   396→\t\truns, err = s.store.ListRuns(ctx, time.Now().Add(-1*time.Hour))\n   397→\t}\n   398→\tif err != nil {\n   399→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"listing runs: %w\", err)\n   400→\t}\n   401→\n   402→\tresp := &pb.ListRunsResponse{}\n   403→\tfor _, run := range runs {\n   404→\t\tresp.Runs = append(resp.Runs, &pb.RunSummary{\n   405→\t\t\tRunId:        run.ID,\n   406→\t\t\tWorkflowName: run.WorkflowName,\n   407→\t\t\tState:        string(run.State),\n   408→\t\t\tStartedAt:    run.StartedAt.String(),\n   409→\t\t\tErrorMessage: run.ErrorMessage,"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_016qqohA26N1zyrzkc6V7p2n","session_id":"8afa4431-c2af-45d7-8651-174f88b0e5d9","uuid":"76a666c0-a23a-4f4c-93bc-6af123eaa6f8"}
[2026-03-13T18:36:12Z] [llm] {"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a11c6ba24710e465c","tool_use_id":"toolu_016qqohA26N1zyrzkc6V7p2n","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Find cleanup container code","usage":{"total_tokens":45639,"tool_uses":28,"duration_ms":54778},"uuid":"805a2ab3-af30-4a4d-8179-1986d496b003","session_id":"8afa4431-c2af-45d7-8651-174f88b0e5d9"}
[2026-03-13T18:36:12Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016qqohA26N1zyrzkc6V7p2n","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have a complete understanding of the cleanup flow. Let me create a comprehensive final report.\n\n## Complete Cleanup Containers Flow Report\n\nI've traced the entire \"Cleanup\" containers functionality from the UI button through to Docker removal. Here's the complete flow:\n\n### 1. **UI Button & Event Handler**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` (lines 77-93)\n\n- **Button Display**: Line 13 - Shows \"Clean up X old container(s)\" button only when `TotalContainerCount > 0`\n- **JavaScript Handler**: `cleanupContainers()` function that:\n  - Disables the button (line 79)\n  - Makes a `DELETE /api/containers` fetch request (line 80)\n  - Handles success response with container count (lines 82-85)\n  - Handles errors gracefully (lines 87-91)\n\n**Project-Level UI:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 473-491)\n- Function `deleteAllContainers()` makes `DELETE /api/projects/{label}/containers` request\n- Updates button with deleted count\n\n### 2. **Container Count Calculation (Backend)**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 290-310)\n\nThe handler calculates `TotalContainerCount` by:\n1. Loading all runs from store (line 292)\n2. Counting runs where `run.ContainerKept == true` per project (lines 293-296)\n3. Summing total across all projects (lines 307-310)\n\n### 3. **API Endpoints & Handlers**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 158-160)\n\nThree distinct DELETE endpoints registered:\n\n```\nDELETE /api/runs/{id}/container           → handleAPIDeleteContainer\nDELETE /api/projects/{name}/containers    → handleAPIDeleteProjectContainers\nDELETE /api/containers                    → handleAPIDeleteAllContainers\n```\n\n#### **Handler: `handleAPIDeleteContainer` (lines 886-922)**\n- Deletes a single container for a specific run\n- Fetches run by ID from store\n- Calls `mgr.Remove()` to delete container\n- Sets `run.ContainerKept = false` and updates store\n- Returns JSON response with status\n\n#### **Handler: `handleAPIDeleteProjectContainers` (lines 925-983)**\n- Mass-deletes all retained/exited containers for a project\n- Lists all runs for project via `h.store.ListRunsByProject()`\n- For each run with `ContainerKept == true` and non-empty `ContainerID`:\n  - Checks container status via `mgr.Inspect()` (line 954)\n  - Skips running containers (line 962-963)\n  - For stopped/exited containers, calls `mgr.Remove()` (line 965)\n  - Updates run record with `ContainerKept = false` (line 969)\n- Returns JSON with `deleted` count and optional `errors` array\n\n#### **Handler: `handleAPIDeleteAllContainers` (lines 986-1037)**\n- Mass-deletes all retained/exited containers across ALL projects\n- Same logic as project-level, but iterates over ALL runs via `h.store.ListRuns()`\n- Returns JSON with aggregated `deleted` count\n\n### 4. **Container Manager Interface**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 65-71)\n\n```go\ntype ContainerManager interface {\n    ContainerLogger\n    Stop(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    Remove(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    Inspect(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (*ports.ContainerStatus, error)\n}\n```\n\n### 5. **Docker Implementation**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`\n\n#### **`Remove()` Method (lines 219-227)**\n- Executes: `docker rm <containerID>`\n- Captures stderr for error reporting\n- Returns formatted error on failure: \"removing container: {stderr}: {err}\"\n\n#### **`Inspect()` Method (lines 229-254)**\n- Executes: `docker inspect --format \"{{.State.Running}} {{.State.ExitCode}} {{.State.FinishedAt}}\"` \n- Parses output to return `ContainerStatus` struct with:\n  - `Running` bool\n  - `ExitCode` int\n  - `FinishedAt` timestamp\n\n#### **`Stop()` Method (lines 154-163)**\n- Executes: `docker stop <containerID>`\n\n### 6. **Container Retention Logic (Run Completion)**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 356-379)\n\nWhen a run completes, the server decides whether to keep or remove container:\n\n**Container is KEPT if:**\n- `--keep-container` flag passed (line 363), OR\n- Run FAILED or was CANCELLED (line 361)\n\n**Container is REMOVED if:**\n- Run succeeded AND no `--keep-container` flag (line 374)\n- Sets `run.ContainerKept = false` in database\n\n### 7. **Data Model**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (line 43)\n\n```go\nContainerKept  bool   // true when the container was retained after run completion\n```\n\n### 8. **Comprehensive Test Coverage**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go`\n\nTests validate:\n- `TestAPIDeleteContainer_Success` (654) - Individual container deletion\n- `TestAPIDeleteProjectContainers_Success` (1309) - Project-level cleanup\n- `TestAPIDeleteProjectContainers_SkipsRunning` (1340) - Running containers not deleted\n- `TestAPIDeleteProjectContainers_SkipsNonKept` (1362) - Non-retained containers skipped\n- `TestAPIDeleteAllContainers_Success` (1966) - Global cleanup\n- `TestAPIDeleteAllContainers_SkipsRunning` (1995) - Running containers protection\n- `TestAPIDeleteAllContainers_SkipsNonKept` (2017) - Non-retained filtering\n- `TestRunsList_CleanupButton` (2043) - Button only shows when containers exist\n- `TestRunsList_NoCleanupButtonWhenNoContainers` (2058) - Button hidden when none retained\n\n---\n\n### Summary of File Locations:\n\n1. **UI Templates**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html`, `project_detail.html`\n2. **Handler/API**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n3. **Docker Runtime**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`\n4. **gRPC Server (retention logic)**: `/workspace/internal/adapters